### Flashing SVITRIX Firmware manually with esptool

If you prefer to flash manually instead of using the web installer.

1. **Install esptool**
   ```bash
   pip install esptool
   ```

2. **Connect Ulanzi TC001**
   Connect via USB-C. Hold BOOT button while pressing EN to enter flash mode.

3. **Flash all partitions (firmware + web UI)**
   ```bash
   esptool.py --chip esp32 --port /dev/ttyUSB0 --baud 460800 write_flash \
     0x1000 bootloader.bin \
     0x8000 partitions.bin \
     0xe000 boot_app0.bin \
     0x10000 firmware.bin \
     0x3C0000 littlefs.bin
   ```

   Replace `/dev/ttyUSB0` with your port (`/dev/tty.usbserial-*` on macOS).

   For a clean install, erase flash first:
   ```bash
   esptool.py --chip esp32 --port /dev/ttyUSB0 erase_flash
   ```

4. **Restart**
   Press EN button. The device will start in AP mode (SVITRIX_XXXX).
   Connect to the AP and open 192.168.4.1 to configure WiFi.

### Partition layout

| Partition | Offset     | Size    | Content           |
|-----------|------------|---------|-------------------|
| bootloader| 0x1000     | 17 KB   | ESP32 bootloader  |
| partitions| 0x8000     | 3 KB    | Partition table   |
| otadata   | 0xE000     | 8 KB    | OTA boot selector |
| app0      | 0x10000    | 1856 KB | Firmware          |
| app1      | 0x1F0000   | 1856 KB | OTA update slot   |
| littlefs  | 0x3C0000   | 256 KB  | Web UI + icons    |
